'''''Republic'' 83''': "Hidden Enemy, Part 3" is the eighty-third and final issue in the ''[[Star Wars: Republic]]'' series of comics. It was published on [[February 8]], [[2006]] by [[Dark Horse Comics]].

==Publisher's summary==
''Palpatine's Order 66 has changed everything. As Jedi are slaughtered across the galaxy, one has managed to cheat fate&mdash;but for how long? Badly wounded by the same troops he previously led to victory, Master Quinlan Vos retreats into the jungle wilderness of the Wookiee homeworld Kashyyyk. As the clones close in, Vos must choose&mdash;stay and fight, or run and put those he loves in danger of the newborn Empire's wrath?''

==Plot summary==
{{Plot|comic}}

==Continuity==
According to [[Randy Stradley]], the fate of [[Quinlan Vos/Legends|Quinlan Vos]] at the end of the comic came directly from [[George Lucas]].<ref name="JCF1">{{JCFCite|url=posts/23104700|board=Literature|thread=Republic #83: The Hidden Enemy, part 3 (of 3)|user=[[Randy Stradley|Randy_Stradley]]|date=2006-02-08|time=11:27 AM|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801160614/https://boards.theforce.net/threads/republic-83-the-hidden-enemy-part-3-of-3.21002752/page-5}}</ref> [[John Ostrander]] had initially considered killing Vos off,<ref name="JCF2">{{JCFCite|url=posts/23122531|board=Literature|thread=Republic #83: The Hidden Enemy, part 3 (of 3)|user=[[John Ostrander|jfostrander]]|date=2006-02-10|time=8:23 AM|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801160441/https://boards.theforce.net/threads/republic-83-the-hidden-enemy-part-3-of-3.21002752/page-8}}</ref> and an interview with [[Jan Duursema]] in ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' before the issue's release claimed that he died.

